<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1629,2014]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="545" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,465,1989,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
In the structure of the phallus this species shows some similarities to 
<taxonomicName authority="MacGowan, 2005" authorityName="MacGowan" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Silba" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="545" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotherayi">
<emphasis box="[1267,1436,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="544">Silba rotherayi</emphasis>
MacGowan, 
<number box="[296,352,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="545" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[422,524,151,176]" name="Malaysia" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
but in that species the basal lobe is more distinctly divided. Other differences in the male genitalia include the presence of long pointed setae at the base of the cerci and long pointed prensisetae in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,282,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Silba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotherayi">
<emphasis box="[151,282,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="545">S. rotherayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
